


                  ::::: HardDisk Installation :::::

1. Unpack archive. It creates own sub-directory called PowerBattle.
2. Add to Your S:Startup-Sequence or S:User-Startup following 3 lines:

     Assign PowerBattle: {path, directory previously created by LhA}
     Assign PBMaps: PowerBattle:Maps
     Assign PBSave: PowerBattle:Save

3. Move s/powerbattle.config to S:
4. Reboot or execute Assigns

Note that first assign's path ends /PowerBattle or :PowerBattle



                 ::::: Floppy Disk Installation :::::

Yes, it is possible. Use your imagination & knowledge! :-|



